transcripts: We're comparing the kitchenaid artisan 5 quart with the newly designed Breville 5-quart mixer. it's the old versus the new and a head-to-head battle . The challenge, the sound of the motor . One reason why mixing is always avoided the solitary experience at home is the sound of the mixer make . So let's just listen to the kitchenaid to the high setting . Shut that down. Now let’s listen to the breville. Just a nice hum. Noticed that the grinding noise is less intrusive than the kitchenaid . The breville hand mixer hear it for yourself; it's built for baking.
